In Uzbekistan, cyber cafes and computer game centers will reopen from December 1, 2020. Gaming centers must comply with the following sanitary and epidemiological requirements:
- players should maintain social distancing;
- employees must wear medical masks and gloves, as well as maintain social distancing;
- visitors should have their body temperature measured, customers with a temperature of 37 degrees and above, with symptoms of infection, and without masks should not be allowed;
- after each visitor, the surfaces of the table and other items must be disinfected.

In Uzbekistan, according to the news report on March 25, 2020, public service centers, registry offices and notaries will be open for emergencies only:
- public service centers assist citizens online and provide service in emergencies only;
- registry offices are open only to register births or deaths;
- notaries assist only with the will, power of attorney, deposit and mortgage-related issues.

